<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Chargé in Bolivia (
                        Adam
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v11</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d17</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">17</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-04-06T18:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-04-06T18:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-06T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="17" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710. Consultation 4/4–646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Adam</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">u.s. urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-06T19:00:00-04:00">April 6, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>292. Foreign Minister<note n="38" xml:id="d17fn38">The Acting Foreign Minister,
                        Col. José Celestino Pinto.</note> personally handed me 1-page memo on
                    Argentine consultation at 7 p.m. Résumé as follows: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Reiterated its memo of Dec. 27, 1945 to this Embassy re erroneous or
                            incomplete information on political situation of American countries
                            which cause judgments [not in?] accordance reality.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>As it is principal interest strengthen American solidarity based on
                            agreements atmosphere of misconfidence must vanish.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>San Francisco Security Pact in order to have regional manifestation in
                            mutual assistance treaty must not exclude any of its members so as to
                            guarantee its effectiveness.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Bolivian Govt feels new conditions for finding complete continental
                            solidarity have arisen as result Argentine elections.</item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>Bolivian Govt declares it will continue to maintain same cordial
                            relations with Argentine Govt as has marked its policy towards all
                            nations of the Continent.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adam</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
